s of providence as prayer, prophecy, and the notion of papal infallibility, teasing out the full range of implications for traditional Christianity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aMolinism. 0aProvidence and government of GodxChristianityxHistory of doctrinesy16th century. 4aPhilosophy. 4aReligious Studies.  aCatholic doctrines.  aJesuit theologian.  aLuis de Molina.  aMolinism.  aMolinist metaphysical perspective.  aMolinist.  aPhilosophical Review.  aReasonableFaith.org.  acatholic theology .  achristian history .  adeterminism.  adivine providence.  ametaphysics of theism.  ametaphysics.  amiddle knowledge.  amoral philosophy.  apapal infallibility .  aphilosopher of religion.  aphilosophical theology.  aphilosophy of religion.  aphilosophy texts.  aprovidence and predestination .  areligious studies .  astudies in philosophy .  astudying religious philosophy .  atheology .08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171185540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501711855423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501711855/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles